    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains three-dimensional information: temporal (quarterly), categorical (product groups), and quantitative (revenue). Synthetic data follows normal distributions (\u03bc=50k, \u03c3=15k) with 15% quarter-over-quarter growth and seasonal variation (Q4 peak). The 3D column chart effectively encodes categorical comparison through color, temporal progression through axis position, and magnitude through column height. Stacking maintains part-to-whole relationships while preserving individual category visibility. Color choices (blue, green, red) follow Cairo's salience principles with 7:1 contrast ratios. Data labels provide exact values while the z-axis rotation gives depth perception without distorting proportions, maintaining Tufte's data-ink ratio by eliminating non-essential gridlines."
